<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dung" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dung,</orth> manure, filth; (cf. <emph>Cow-dung, Dung-hill</emph>): <cit><quote>never palates more the d., the beggars' nurse and Caesars',</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 7</bibl></cit> (cf. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 1, 35</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.444" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 444</bibl>. Some M. Edd. <emph>dug!</emph>）
